## S3. Upvote on Launch Page

🚨 **Click the inner SVG/span element — this triggers React event handler.

**ONE evaluate — check + click + verify:**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var btn = document.querySelector('button[data-test=\"vote-button\"].w-full'); if (!btn) return { error: 'no main vote button' }; if (btn.innerText.trim().includes('Upvoted')) return { alreadyUpvoted: true }; btn.scrollIntoView({ block: 'center' }); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var inner = btn.querySelector('svg') || btn.querySelector('span') || btn.firstElementChild; if (!inner) return { error: 'no inner element' }; inner.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true, view: window })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var upvoted = btn.innerText.trim().includes('Upvoted'); return { upvoted: upvoted }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

Only increment `daily.upvotes.current` if `upvoted: true`.

## S4. Extract Maker Username

🚨 **Prefer using S7 Step 3 combined evaluate instead** — it returns `makerUsername` along with comment verification. Only use S4 standalone if you need maker BEFORE commenting.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const links = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a')); const makerLink = links.find(a => { const href = a.href || ''; if (!href.includes('/@')) return false; const parent = a.parentElement; return parent && parent.innerText && parent.innerText.includes('Maker'); }); const makerUsername = makerLink ? makerLink.href.match(/@([^/?]+)/)?.[1] : null; return { makerUsername }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

## S5. Check Follow Button State

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); const followBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Follow'); const alreadyFollowing = btns.some(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Following'); return { followBtn: !!followBtn, alreadyFollowing }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

"Follow" button: find via evaluate and click

## S6. Streak Keeper (Homepage Upvote)

Homepage vote buttons work with JS `.click()` (unlike launch pages).

**Click:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const btn = document.querySelector('button[data-test=\"vote-button\"]'); if (!btn) return { error: 'vote_btn_not_found' }; const filledDiv = btn.querySelector('[data-filled]'); if (filledDiv && filledDiv.getAttribute('data-filled') === 'true') return { skipped: true, reason: 'already_upvoted' }; btn.click(); return { clicked: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Verify (1.5s wait embedded — NO separate sleep step):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const btn = document.querySelector('button[data-test=\"vote-button\"]'); const filledDiv = btn ? btn.querySelector('[data-filled]') : null; const filled = filledDiv ? filledDiv.getAttribute('data-filled') : 'none'; return { verified: filled === 'true', text: btn ? btn.innerText.trim() : 'N/A' }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

## S7. Comment on a Launch

50+ buttons have `type="submit"` on PH pages. NEVER match by type. ALWAYS match `b.innerText.trim() === "Comment"`.

❌ **Do NOT add a separate scroll step** — `document.querySelector('.tiptap.ProseMirror')` finds the editor regardless of viewport scroll. Scroll wastes 1 step per product.

**Step 1 — Set text (1.5s wait embedded — NO separate sleep step):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const editor = document.querySelector('.tiptap.ProseMirror'); if (!editor) return { error: 'editor_not_found' }; editor.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll', false, null); document.execCommand('delete', false, null); document.execCommand('insertText', false, window.__data.text); return { set: true, text: editor.textContent.slice(0, 50) }; }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_COMMENT_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 2 — Click Comment (1.5s wait embedded — NO separate sleep step):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const buttons = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); const submitBtn = buttons.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Comment'); if (!submitBtn) return { error: 'comment_btn_not_found', available: buttons.map(b => b.innerText.trim()).filter(t => t.length > 0 && t.length < 20).slice(0, 15) }; if (submitBtn.disabled) return { error: 'comment_btn_disabled' }; submitBtn.click(); return { clicked: true, buttonText: submitBtn.innerText.trim() }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 3 — Verify + Extract maker (3s wait — ONE evaluate, NO separate steps):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const editor = document.querySelector('.tiptap.ProseMirror'); const editorText = editor ? editor.textContent.trim() : ''; const editorEmpty = editorText.length < 5; const url = window.location.href; const links = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a')); const makerLink = links.find(a => { const href = a.href || ''; if (!href.includes('/@')) return false; const parent = a.parentElement; return parent && parent.innerText && parent.innerText.includes('Maker'); }); const m = makerLink ? makerLink.href.match(/@([^/?]+)/) : null; return { submitted: editorEmpty, editorText: editorText.slice(0, 60), url: url, urlChanged: !url.includes('producthunt.com/products/') && !url.includes('producthunt.com/posts/'), makerUsername: m ? m[1] : null }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

- `submitted: false` → retry steps 2-3 once
- `urlChanged: true` → wrong button clicked, navigate back, retry from step 1
- Max 2 total attempts. Fail → log Error, skip.
- Use `makerUsername` from this result directly — do NOT call S4 separately.

## S9. Batch Upvote on Homepage

Homepage vote buttons work with JS `.click()`.

**Single evaluate — count before, click, wait, count after (ONE step, NO separate sleep):**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { const btns = document.querySelectorAll('button[data-test=\"vote-button\"]'); let votedBefore = 0; for (const btn of btns) { const filled = btn.querySelector('[data-filled]'); if (filled && filled.getAttribute('data-filled') === 'true') votedBefore++; } const maxUpvotes = window.__data.maxUpvotes; let clicked = 0; for (const btn of btns) { if (clicked >= maxUpvotes) break; const filled = btn.querySelector('[data-filled]'); if (filled && filled.getAttribute('data-filled') === 'true') continue; btn.click(); clicked++; } await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); let votedAfter = 0; for (const btn of btns) { const filled = btn.querySelector('[data-filled]'); if (filled && filled.getAttribute('data-filled') === 'true') votedAfter++; } const delta = votedAfter - votedBefore; return { clicked, votedBefore, votedAfter, delta, verified: delta === clicked }; }", "data": {"maxUpvotes": 2}}
ENDJSON
```

Update `daily.upvotes.current` by adding `delta` (NOT `clicked` — delta is the verified count).
